com.ebay.lightning.client.caller

Interface ServiceCaller

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EmbeddedAPICaller, RestAPICaller

    public interface ServiceCaller
    ServiceCaller acts as a interface between the client and core (aka seeds). This interface provides the methods to make reservation, submit tasks, poll the task response, get audit data, view/edit configuration etc.
    Author:
    shashukla
    See Also:
    RestAPICaller, EmbeddedAPICaller

    • Method Detail

      • reserve

        com.ebay.lightning.core.beans.ReservationReceipt reserve(int count,
                                                         String serviceHostIp)
        Attempts to reserve task execution bandwidth on the seed
        Parameters:
        count - load size of the request
        serviceHostIp - the seed
        Returns:
        reservation receipt for the requested bandwidth. The seed might return ACCEPTED, DENIED or BUSY based on the current work load size of the seed.

      • getAuditReport

        com.ebay.lightning.core.store.LightningRequestReport getAuditReport(String sessionId,
                                                                    String serviceHostIp)
        Get the audit report for the request id in compressed format.
        Parameters:
        sessionId - the session id submitted through submit(LightningRequest, String) method or returned by the reserve(int, String) method
        serviceHostIp - the seed
        Returns:
        the audit report for the session id in compressed format. Returns the consolidated report if the session id is not present in the seed
